  </table>
</div>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Verdana" size="2">There
are four parts to every arrow. <a href="#Nocks:">Groove Nocks</a>, <a href="#Shafts:">Shafts</a>,
<a href="#Tips:">Tips</a>, and <a href="#Fletches:">Fletches</a>. And you will
need one of each part for every arrow that you make. Now there are different qualities
for each part, and the better the quality of the part, the harder it will be to
make an arrow with that part. And consequently the better the quality of the
part the more expensive it will be to buy. Here is a break down of each part and
how difficult it is to make an arrow with that part.</font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0" align="center"><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Fletching">Top</a></font></p>
