				Ok quick clarifacation The trueshot can be made by a fletcher of 1 skill or 250 the chances of makeing one at skill 1 is slim to nill I made one on my second try with 80 fletching so its not required to be at least 150 skill (although that helps alot) the components are Spiderling Silk, Micro Servo, Dwarven Wire, and Treant Wood shards. combine in the materials pack it then becomes closed take that to Maesyn Trueshot (spelled wrong I know) who STARTS the quest in Kelethin at the ranger guild (where else) he gives you a Treant Bow staff, You then put that along with one micro servo and one dwarven wire hit combine and hope it doesnt fail if you succeed you get a trueshot bow. Oh wait almost forgot you must have a planeing tool in with the Staff Wire and Servo. Which can be purchased at just about any fletching supply store that sells bow supplies (havent seen many arrow part merchants selling planeing tools)<BR>
